{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17595294","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17595294"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:02:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:02:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15346"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15346","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15346"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.78,0.12,0.05,0.02,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8037"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69736"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8037","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8037"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15346"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55190"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"363"},{"type":"tags","id":"688"},{"type":"tags","id":"1044"},{"type":"tags","id":"1109"},{"type":"tags","id":"4847"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7567"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19521"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19523"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69736","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/69736"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA paediatrician is discussing common causes of constipation in children with medical students.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most common cause of constipation in children?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Withholding behaviour","Hirschsprung disease","Hypothyroidism","Hypercalcaemia","Coeliac disease"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWithholding behaviour\u003C/strong\u003E is the most common cause of constipation in children, often developing after a painful or unpleasant bowel movement, resulting in fear and subsequent stool retention. This creates a vicious cycle as retained stool in the colon and rectum becomes harder with increased water absorption and eventually more difficult and painful to pass.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther precipitating factors of functional constipation include bowel habit (children may ignore the urge to defecate), change in toilet environment (e.g. unfamiliar toilets at daycare or school) and diet (inadequate fibre intake)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile organic causes exist, they are much less common:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHirschsprung disease\u003C/strong\u003E presents with delayed passage of meconium and chronic constipation from birth\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E can cause constipation through decreased gut motility\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypercalcaemia\u003C/strong\u003E may lead to constipation through effects on smooth muscle function\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoeliac disease\u003C/strong\u003E more typically presents with diarrhoea, though constipation can occur in some cases\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Functional constipation is the most common cause of childhood constipation, often triggered by withholding behaviour.","Organic causes of childhood constipation include Hirschsprung disease, hypothyroidism, hypercalcaemia, and coeliac disease."],"references":["Bolia R, Safe M, Southwell BR, King SK, Oliver MR. Paediatric constipation for general paediatricians: Review using a case-based and evidence-based approach. J Paediatr Child Health. 2020 Nov;56(11):1708-1718. doi: 10.1111/jpc.14720. PMID: 33197982","Constipation in children and young people: diagnosis and management. London: National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE); 2017 Jul. (NICE Clinical Guidelines, No. 99.) Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK554924/","Pawasarat A, Biank VF. Constipation in Pediatrics: A Clinical Review. Pediatr Ann. 2021 Aug;50(8):e320-e324. doi: 10.3928/19382359-20210714-01. Epub 2021 Aug 1. PMID: 34398719","Kids Health Info : Constipation [Internet]. www.rch.org.au. Available from: https://www.rch.org.au/kidsinfo/fact_sheets/Constipation/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55190"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15346"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55190","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55190"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-12T15:40:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-13T18:48:39+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8037"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69736"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10